". . . for I do always those things that please him"
(John 6:38;
John 8:29).

"For behold, the Lord hath said: I will not succor my people in the day of their transgression;
but I will hedge up their ways that they prosper not; and their doings shall be as a stumbling
block before them" (Mosiah 7:29).
